#################
#  GC SETTINGS  #
#################



### Heap Settings
## Set production defaults (8GB heap) for time-series workloads
## Override with MAX_HEAP_SIZE env var if needed
-Xms8G
-Xmx8G

### Shenandoah GC Settings
## Changed from G1GC to Shenandoah for better latency with time-series workloads
-XX:+UseShenandoahGC
-XX:+AlwaysPreTouch

# G1-specific options (disabled when using Shenandoah):
# -XX:+ParallelRefProcEnabled
# -XX:MaxTenuringThreshold=2
# -XX:G1HeapRegionSize=16m

# G1-specific settings (all disabled for Shenandoah):
# -XX:+UnlockExperimentalVMOptions
# -XX:G1NewSizePercent=50
# -XX:G1RSetUpdatingPauseTimePercent=5
# -XX:MaxGCPauseMillis=300
# -XX:InitiatingHeapOccupancyPercent=70
# -XX:ParallelGCThreads=16
# -XX:ConcGCThreads=16

# Shenandoah uses its own concurrent marking and compaction
# No additional tuning needed for basic operation


